question.title:
Consent form for volunteers for the study
This short experiment is part of a larger project:
Human cooperation: A multimodal approach experiments with women with Borderline personality disorder (MenKoopBPS)
I read the information sheet (available at http://www.dnhi-lab.org/ethics_online_en) for the experiment and also had the opportunity to contact Mr Korn by phone or email to get detailed and comprehensible answers to questions about the aim and procedure of the study as well as about the risks. I had the opportunity to ask questions during the telephone call or the contact by e-mail. All my questions were answered to my satisfaction. I voluntarily agreed to participate in the study. I had sufficient time to make my decision. I received a copy of the information leaflet and the consent form.
Data protection I have been informed and agree that my data collected in the study, in particular information about my health, may be recorded in pseudonymised form, evaluated and possibly also passed on in pseudonymised form, possibly also to countries with lower data protection requirements. Third parties will not be given access to personal records. My name will also not be mentioned when the results of the study are published. Your personal data will be kept for a maximum of 10 years after the end of the study. As soon as it is possible according to the purpose of the research, but after 10 years at the latest, the personal data will be anonymised and the anonymised data will be stored indefinitely. The data will be published in anonymised form when the results are published, provided that publication of the data does not allow any inference to your person.
How old are you (rounded to the nearest year)?
Which country do you currently live in?
Is there anything you would like to tell us about the study? Any feedback is greatly appreciated.

The situation is almost identical to the last one: you and someone else (this will be a different 'other' person than in the first decision, someone else) decide between A and B, not knowing what the other will decide. The amounts of money are the same, but now they are ordered differently.
Please pay careful attention to the numbers below and then make your decision. Please decide afresh - you can make the same decision as before, or make a different decision, just choose the option that suits you best, given this new situation.
